    report

    report.Rd

    Log file function: print a character string or a data object into a same output file.

    report(
  data,
  output = "results.txt",
  path,
  overwrite = FALSE,
  rownames.kept = FALSE,
  vector.cat = FALSE,
  noquote = TRUE,
  sep = 2
)

    Arguments

    data

    Object to print in the output file. If NULL, nothing is done, with no warning.

    output

    Single character string. Name of the output file.

    path

    Location of the output file.

    overwrite

    Single logical value. If output file already exists, defines if the printing is appended (default FALSE) or if the output file content is erased before printing (TRUE).

    rownames.kept

    Single logical value. Defines whether row names have to be removed or not in small tables (less than length.rows rows).

    vector.cat

    Single logical value. If TRUE print a vector of length > 1 using cat() instead of capture.output(). Otherwise (default FALSE) the opposite.

    noquote

    Single logical value. If TRUE no quote are present for the characters.

    sep

    Single integer representing the number of empty lines after printed data.

    Value

    Nothing.

    Details

    REQUIRED PACKAGES

    none

    REQUIRED FUNCTIONS FROM CUTE_LITTLE_R_FUNCTION

    arg_check()

    Examples

    #report()
report(data = 1:3, output = "results.txt", path = ".", overwrite = TRUE, 
rownames.kept = FALSE, vector.cat = FALSE, noquote = FALSE, sep = 2)
